      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a superlative example of lightweight JDM engineering, preserved in showroom-caliber condition. It features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression and seamless boost transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbines. The chassis retains its factory-spec structural integrity, supported by a four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for precise torque vectoring. Every vacuum line in the complex control system has been meticulously maintained, ensuring the high-revving powerband remains linear and responsive. With an immaculate undercarriage and a cooling system optimized for thermal efficiency, this FD3S offers a rare, mechanically pure driving experience for the dedicated enthusiast.",
